WEBVTT

00:02.068 --> 00:03.558
Previously on Boston Legal.

00:03.670 --> 00:05.695
I used to work on
the Texas Innocence Project.

00:05.805 --> 00:08.774
One of my cases is up on appeal.
I could use your help.

00:08.875 --> 00:11.708
I'm looking for the best lawyer
I can find. I think that's you.

00:11.811 --> 00:14.712
- I don't like jibber-jabber in my courtroom.
- Oh, my goodness.

00:14.814 --> 00:17.180
- That's as far as you should go.
- Shejust kissed you?

00:17.283 --> 00:20.514
- I'm not gonna pursue it.
- He shoots a client in the knee.

00:20.620 --> 00:24.249
- He then shoots a homeless man
with a paintball gun.

00:24.357 --> 00:27.588
- Could you kindly point in any
direction other than my head?

00:27.694 --> 00:29.127
It's not loaded.

00:29.229 --> 00:31.891
- Oh, I guess it is.
- For God's sake, Denny!

00:38.905 --> 00:43.171
It's just that I feel
my song is still in me.

00:43.276 --> 00:45.642
- What song?
- My song.

00:45.745 --> 00:48.805
Everybody has a song in them, Sydney.
You should know that.

00:48.915 --> 00:51.748
Oh, I see.
And yours is still unsung.

00:51.851 --> 00:53.751
- Is that it?
- Yeah.

00:53.853 --> 00:56.151
I mean, here I am in my 70s...

00:56.256 --> 01:00.886
and I still feel that everything
I wanted to express in life...

01:00.994 --> 01:06.455
is still bottled up inside me
like a- a kidney stone.

01:08.168 --> 01:10.830
Talk to me, Sydney.
What are you thinking?

01:10.937 --> 01:14.134
- I think you're bored, Denny.
- Bored?

01:14.240 --> 01:16.435
How can I be bored?
I'm Denny Crane.

01:16.543 --> 01:18.773
Even the sound
of my name fascinates.

01:18.878 --> 01:22.075
More, Sydney.
More about me.

01:22.182 --> 01:24.377
Yeah. Okay.

01:25.485 --> 01:27.749
Well, I think...

01:27.854 --> 01:30.789
that you are a silver-spoon-fed...

01:30.890 --> 01:33.415
rich, empty sack...

01:33.526 --> 01:36.427
who has nothing to do now
but count his money...

01:36.529 --> 01:39.760
or spend it on hookers...

01:39.866 --> 01:43.825
and therapists who offer up
some form of affirmation.

01:43.937 --> 01:46.132
And, frankly, I'm sick of it!

01:46.239 --> 01:49.367
I would no longer even treat you...

01:49.476 --> 01:52.104
but for the $600 an hour I charge.

01:52.212 --> 01:54.476
Which sum, I might assure you...

01:54.581 --> 01:57.277
is meant to deter
your recurring visits.

01:57.383 --> 01:59.214
Do you understand me, Denny?

01:59.319 --> 02:03.346
I would sooner leap from the window
than see your lips move...

02:03.456 --> 02:06.323
the sight of which
is the visual cue...

02:06.426 --> 02:10.362
that feculent blather
is about to spew forth.

02:12.198 --> 02:15.133
This is no way for a therapist
to talk to a patient.

02:15.235 --> 02:19.035
My official medical recommendation
would be that you take yoga classes...

02:19.139 --> 02:23.633
so that you might gain the necessary flexibility
to stick your head up your ass.

02:30.717 --> 02:33.618
I- I do feel like
an empty sack sometimes.

02:33.720 --> 02:37.850
It occasions depression. It even caused me
to buy a handgun to end it.

02:37.957 --> 02:40.926
I even carry it around with me...

02:41.027 --> 02:46.192
never knowing when I might
decide to join the ranks of the unliving.

02:46.299 --> 02:50.531
And then I think to myself,
how unoriginal.

02:50.637 --> 02:53.504
Suicide is so ordinary.

02:53.606 --> 02:56.234
But...

02:56.342 --> 02:59.402
if I were to shoot
my doctor-

02:59.512 --> 03:01.446
Well!

03:01.548 --> 03:03.448
Ah, now, but, you see, Denny...

03:03.550 --> 03:06.212
that would result in you
actually accomplishing something real.

03:06.319 --> 03:08.617
You see?
Something actual...

03:08.721 --> 03:13.886
as opposed to the manufactured heroics
of your publicist, the mad cow-

03:13.993 --> 03:18.521
And then it suddenly might matter-
really matter- that you were born.

03:18.631 --> 03:22.226
And-And how would you
handle that after 70-plus years...

03:22.335 --> 03:24.565
of unmitigated insignificance?

03:27.974 --> 03:31.432
- You don't think I matter?
- Oh, pull the trigger, Denny! Do something...

03:31.544 --> 03:35.241
to rise above your insipid
press releases!

03:35.348 --> 03:38.215
All the meaninglessness!
Just pull it!

03:38.318 --> 03:40.809
You think I won't?

03:40.920 --> 03:43.616
Actually, I happen to know you will.
I happen to know you must.

03:43.723 --> 03:46.817
You see, you're pointing a gun
at a therapist...

03:46.926 --> 03:49.656
who's not only got
a death wish of his own...

03:49.762 --> 03:53.220
but also a life insurance policy
which excludes suicide.

03:53.333 --> 03:55.665
And, you see, Denny,
I've often wondered...

03:55.768 --> 04:00.000
how can I possibly end my life without
forfeiting my son's Harvard education?

04:00.106 --> 04:03.234
But if I were to be
murdered, then-

04:03.343 --> 04:05.311
So...

04:06.746 --> 04:10.512
you must shoot me,
or I will shoot you.

04:10.617 --> 04:12.983
Go ahead. Pull the trigger,
or I will kill you.

04:16.189 --> 04:18.987
- Okay, Sydney.
- Pull it.

04:19.091 --> 04:22.186
- I'm not gonna shoot you. Don't be ridiculous.
- Then you must die.

04:22.295 --> 04:26.425
- Come on, Sydney. Game's over.
- Give you the count of three. One-

04:27.533 --> 04:29.433
- Sydney.
- Two.

04:29.535 --> 04:31.867
- For God's sake.
- Three.

