What now?

05:25.325 --> 05:27.020
Denny shot his therapist.

05:27.126 --> 05:30.095
Dear God. Paintball?

05:30.196 --> 05:33.256
- Real bullets.
- Is he-

05:33.366 --> 05:36.358
No. The man is apparently going to survive.
He's in the hospital.

05:36.469 --> 05:39.438
Denny's in custody.
Where's Alan?

05:41.307 --> 05:44.037
It's not that I'm not ready, Your Honor!

05:44.143 --> 05:47.772
It's that I was called for trial.
Division Six, Judge Holt.

05:47.880 --> 05:49.848
Judge Holt doesn't
control my courtroom.

05:49.949 --> 05:53.180
I told you the last time there'd be
no further continuances.

05:53.286 --> 05:55.584
I cannot be in two places
at the same time!

05:55.688 --> 05:59.021
- You should've gotten somebody else from your office to cover.
- Somebody else?

05:59.125 --> 06:01.423
The public defender's office
is so overextended.

06:01.527 --> 06:03.893
So's the D. A. 's office.
He's here and ready.

06:03.996 --> 06:08.023
Of course he's ready.
Because they prioritize the racial profiling cases.

06:08.134 --> 06:11.433
- I object to that, Your Honor.
- The truth is we shouldn't even be here!

06:11.537 --> 06:16.304
Save it for trial, counsel. Which will begin
tomorrow, either with or without you.

06:16.409 --> 06:18.104
Adjourned.

06:25.685 --> 06:27.778
Excuse me.
I couldn't help but overhear...

06:27.887 --> 06:30.185
which is so often
the case when people shout.

06:30.289 --> 06:33.315
My name is Alan Shore.
I'm an extraordinary attorney.

06:33.426 --> 06:37.226
I could tell you stories.
But more incredibly, I'm available.

06:40.900 --> 06:43.460
Alan.

06:43.569 --> 06:46.265
- Chelina.
- Oh, my God.

06:46.372 --> 06:48.932
- How are you?
- I'm fine.

06:49.041 --> 06:51.100
How are you?

06:51.210 --> 06:54.839
Today, a little dyspeptic.
But in general, I'm splendid.

06:54.947 --> 06:58.781
- God. The last time I saw you-
- I think it was a Sunday.

06:58.885 --> 07:03.447
Then I was taken off the air. You went off to
do movies. Then I got switched to Tuesdays and-

07:03.556 --> 07:05.649
Here we are, with old footage.

07:05.758 --> 07:09.091
Exactly.
You look smashing.

07:10.363 --> 07:12.331
And you're black.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.332
- Sorry?
- This is fate.

07:14.434 --> 07:17.460
I just took a case where
I think race was a factor.

07:17.570 --> 07:20.903
Profiling. I'd love to
exploit you...

07:21.007 --> 07:23.498
which I believe
you invited me to do once.

07:23.609 --> 07:25.941
- I meant sexually.
- Yes.

07:26.045 --> 07:31.108
So, this case involves persecution,
civil rights- all the good stuff.

07:31.217 --> 07:34.015
- Can Legal Aid spare you? The client's indigent.
- Alan...

07:34.120 --> 07:37.180
the last time we worked together,
I kissed you.

07:37.290 --> 07:40.453
Really? I'd forgotten.
You'll have to refresh me on that.

07:40.560 --> 07:42.824
Excuse me.

07:44.730 --> 07:47.130
My lover.

07:47.233 --> 07:49.861
Hello, Denny.

07:49.969 --> 07:52.699
You did what?

08:21.667 --> 08:24.329
- I thought he was a quail.
- I'm not laughing.

08:24.437 --> 08:26.997
It was total self-defense.

08:27.106 --> 08:30.598
After I threatened to kill him,
the bastard threatened to kill me. It's not right.

08:30.710 --> 08:33.178
- Why were you carrying the gun?
- I have a constitutional right to.

08:33.279 --> 08:35.246
- Not a concealed weapon.
- Oh, yes, I do.

08:35.347 --> 08:37.248
And the Supreme Court's
gonna say so.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.341
Just as soon as they finish
overturning Roe v. Wade.

08:41.120 --> 08:43.587
Denny, this time
you've gone way too far.

08:43.688 --> 08:45.850
You always say that.

08:45.958 --> 08:49.018
No, I don't. Paul Lewiston does.
And besides, you shot a man. Another man.

08:49.128 --> 08:53.258
I'm telling you I had no choice.
The man was gonna kill me.

08:53.366 --> 08:56.563
He could go tojail for this.
I mean, how could he avoid it?

08:56.669 --> 08:58.569
First of all,
he's claiming self-defense.

08:58.671 --> 09:01.469
Second, the guy's apparently okay.
He just took it in the clavicle.

09:01.574 --> 09:05.567
- Third, I'm talking about Denny. He shoots people all the time.
- Well, you're probably right.

09:05.678 --> 09:08.476
He's probably already booked
himself on Larry King Live.

09:11.017 --> 09:13.952
- What's happening with Sandy?
- Nothing.

09:14.053 --> 09:16.578
- I thought you were gonna-
- Nothing's happening with Sandy.

09:16.689 --> 09:19.590
- Didn't you have your big second-
- Nothing's happening with Sandy.

09:21.761 --> 09:24.491
She dumped me.

09:24.597 --> 09:26.827
I'm sorry.

09:26.933 --> 09:29.902
- Did she say why?
- Does it really matter?

09:30.002 --> 09:34.336
Brad, while I appreciate how deeply guarded
you are, you need to share more.

09:34.440 --> 09:37.637
- I mean, you don't have any friends to talk to.
- I have plenty.

09:37.743 --> 09:40.507
Name three.

09:40.613 --> 09:42.911
What happened?

09:43.015 --> 09:45.108
You know, I'm going to tell you.

09:45.217 --> 09:49.415
Just to see if the look on your face
remotely matches the look on mine when she-

09:49.522 --> 09:51.786
- You know why she dumped me?
- Hmm?

09:51.891 --> 09:54.587
Because I'm a lousy kisser.

09:54.694 --> 09:56.958
Yeah. Exactly my reaction.

09:57.063 --> 09:59.896
Well, um, all I can say...

09:59.999 --> 10:01.967
if that is in fact
the reason-

10:02.068 --> 10:04.127
- It is.
- You're sure?

10:04.236 --> 10:06.329
- I called an ex-girlfriend. She confirmed it.
- Confirmed?

10:06.439 --> 10:09.806
I'm the worst kisser
in the history of the planet.

10:09.909 --> 10:11.433
Oh.

10:11.544 --> 10:13.876
Yeah. Let me ask you something.

10:13.980 --> 10:16.710
Is it really that important
in the scheme of a relationship...

10:16.816 --> 10:20.217
and all its potential, including but not
limited to the parenting of children-

10:20.319 --> 10:22.549
Is how a man kisses
really that important?

10:22.655 --> 10:26.716
Well, at the beginning,
all the promise of romance...

10:26.826 --> 10:28.138
and forgive me,
but the magic, it's-

10:28.173 --> 10:29.450
and forgive me,
but the magic, it's-

10:29.562 --> 10:31.496
Yes, it's in the kiss.

10:31.597 --> 10:34.566
Women are always complaining
about not being taken seriously.

10:34.667 --> 10:37.966
And you look at the leading women's
magazines- Vogue, Cosmopolitan-

10:38.070 --> 10:42.803
it's always about "How do I get a man?"
"How do I look?" "How do I please a man in bed?"

10:42.908 --> 10:47.038
And now I discover they're willing to measure
the substance of a relationship with a kiss.

10:47.146 --> 10:51.139
It isn't men who demean women.
It's women.

11:00.593 --> 11:02.493
Hey. Alan. How's it going?

11:02.595 --> 11:05.496
Fine. Thanks. How are you?
You can get back to me on that.

11:05.598 --> 11:08.658
If there's something trapped in there,
I encourage you to let it out quickly.

11:08.768 --> 11:10.929
I'm due in court.

11:11.037 --> 11:14.564
Well, I was wondering if I could join you
and Denny on the balcony sometime.

11:14.674 --> 11:18.303
Just trying to diversify
my life with some male bonding...

11:18.411 --> 11:20.936
and I was wondering, you know-

11:21.047 --> 11:24.539
Brad, any gathering of three or more men
always seems like a team to me...

11:24.650 --> 11:26.641
and I've never been
much of a team player.

11:26.752 --> 11:28.720
So if you're going to show,
count me out.

11:28.821 --> 11:31.790
But is there something specific
you'd like to talk about?

11:34.160 --> 11:36.128
Are you a good kisser?

11:45.237 --> 11:48.206
Case number 62345.

11:48.307 --> 11:50.707
The Commonwealth versus
Denny Crane. Attempted-

11:50.810 --> 11:54.143
Alan Shore for the defendant.
We'll waive reading of the charges.

11:54.246 --> 11:57.374
- Oh, dear God, it's you.
- I know who I am, counsel.

11:57.483 --> 11:59.815
You don't need to tell me it's me.

11:59.919 --> 12:02.149
I know perfectly well it's me.

12:02.254 --> 12:06.486
That's superfluous information
that is tantamount to jibber-jabber.

12:06.592 --> 12:09.220
I do not tolerate
jibber-jabber in my courtroom.

12:09.328 --> 12:12.593
The defense enters a plea of not guilty.
I move for a probable cause hearing.

12:12.698 --> 12:14.757
- Why?
- Why?

12:14.867 --> 12:17.802
- First, because I'm entitled to.
Second, because I think- - He shot him.

12:17.903 --> 12:20.838
The victim is in the hospital.

12:20.940 --> 12:23.841
I think I have enough
probable cause, Mr. Shoop.

12:23.943 --> 12:26.104
Actually, Your Honor,
uh, since our last get-together...

12:26.212 --> 12:28.112
I've changed my name
from Shoop to Shore.

12:28.214 --> 12:30.682
Since it's already on
my driver's license and passport...

12:30.783 --> 12:33.047
not to mention
all the pleadings before you-

12:33.152 --> 12:35.279
Though I'd never presume you
to read pleadings. They're-

12:35.387 --> 12:37.082
- Jibber-jabber.
- Jibber-jabber.

12:37.189 --> 12:39.885
The victim is in fact scheduled
to be released from the hospital today.

12:39.992 --> 12:43.450
It was simply a shoulder wound, which is where
my client was hoping the bullet would land...

12:43.562 --> 12:47.157
once the gun accidentally went off
after the victim threatened to shoot my client...

12:47.266 --> 12:50.030
- putting him in reasonable fear for his life.
- Your Honor, ifhe wants...

12:50.136 --> 12:52.502
a probable cause hearing,
let him call the arresting officer.

12:52.605 --> 12:56.006
The arresting officer wasn't there.
It was only my client and Dr. Fields.

12:56.108 --> 12:58.099
We're talking about
attempted murder here.

12:58.210 --> 13:00.678
The damage to Mr. Crane's reputation
could be irreparable.

13:00.780 --> 13:04.443
These charges never should've been filed.
I should be allowed a probable cause hearing.

13:04.550 --> 13:06.677
You talk too much.

13:06.786 --> 13:10.552
Assuming the victim
is physically able...

13:10.656 --> 13:15.525
we will reconvene at 3.00 p. m.
tomorrow, you talker.

13:15.628 --> 13:20.156
Enough of this- this... "poopycock. "

13:20.266 --> 13:21.563
Poopycock.

13:21.667 --> 13:23.567
Poopycock.

13:32.845 --> 13:36.406
Oh, no. No, no. No, no.
No, you don't. Get out, Denny.

13:36.515 --> 13:38.745
Dr. Fields, I'm Alan Shore.

13:38.851 --> 13:43.550
You undoubtedly know by now that we've subpoenaed
you to appear at a probable cause hearing.

13:43.656 --> 13:47.820
Well, that's not a very wise ploy, Mr. Shore.
What is it you expect me to say?

13:47.927 --> 13:49.485
That you forced Denny
to shoot you-

13:49.595 --> 13:52.086
that you gave him no choice.

13:52.198 --> 13:55.395
Oh, you don't want to be calling me
to the stand, okay?

13:55.501 --> 13:57.992
Dr. Fields, Denny informed me...

13:58.103 --> 14:00.663
that your intense desire to die...

14:00.773 --> 14:03.173
played a significant part
in what happened.

14:03.275 --> 14:05.243
You know, often when people
contemplate dying...

14:05.344 --> 14:08.074
they take measure of their legacy.

14:08.180 --> 14:12.082
I'm assuming yours thus far
consists of many things.

14:12.184 --> 14:14.049
Denny assured me
honesty is one of them.

14:14.153 --> 14:18.021
I shall count on you to be honest
in that witness chair tomorrow, sir.

14:18.123 --> 14:22.890
Well, now, I wouldn't count
on anything if I were you.

14:22.995 --> 14:26.954
Sydney, I never would've shot you.
You know that.

14:44.984 --> 14:47.646
Dear God, what now?

14:47.753 --> 14:50.085
The managing partners
have convened a meeting.

14:50.189 --> 14:52.749
The topic of discussion
is deposing Denny...

14:52.858 --> 14:54.985
expelling him from the firm.

14:55.094 --> 14:57.494
What? First of all,
the financial hit would-

14:57.596 --> 14:59.461
They don't care.
They've had enough.

14:59.565 --> 15:02.557
Second of all, they need to read
their partnership agreement. Denny can-

15:02.668 --> 15:05.398
Evidently we need to read it.
There is a clause...

15:05.504 --> 15:07.438
which calls for his ouster...

15:07.539 --> 15:09.803
should he ever be convicted of a felony, which-

15:09.909 --> 15:11.809
he is certainly looking at now.

15:15.247 --> 15:17.272
What do we do now?

15:17.383 --> 15:20.546
I don't know.
They seem serious.

15:20.653 --> 15:22.712
Why shouldn't they be?

15:22.821 --> 15:24.789
He shoots people.

15:28.127 --> 15:30.391
Massachusetts has no
"stop and identify"statutes.

15:30.496 --> 15:33.021
So we could make the argument
that the arrest was unlawful...

15:33.132 --> 15:35.327
and therefore our client
had a right to resist.

15:35.434 --> 15:37.925
- That'll never fly.
- Well, it doesn't need to fly...

15:38.037 --> 15:41.495
so much as flap and flutter
its way to reasonable doubt.

15:41.607 --> 15:45.941
Profiling is wrong. We certainly
don't do it when selling off our ports.

15:47.279 --> 15:49.008
Why are you looking at me like that?

15:49.114 --> 15:50.979
Who's closing here?

15:51.083 --> 15:52.880
Sorry?

15:52.985 --> 15:56.113
With the case.
Should I close or you?

15:56.221 --> 15:58.689
Uh, I'll take the client...

15:58.791 --> 16:01.055
and you can close.

16:01.160 --> 16:03.526
Alan.

16:03.629 --> 16:05.597
May I?

16:09.001 --> 16:11.902
I'm not terribly comfortable with you
working closely with this woman.

16:13.005 --> 16:14.973
- What?
- I'm tapped into office gossip.

16:15.074 --> 16:18.202
I happen to know you kissed her
during the death penalty thingy case.

16:18.310 --> 16:21.040
You're kissing me now.
Remember?

16:21.146 --> 16:24.912
Melissa, you and I kissed once.
I barely participated.

16:25.017 --> 16:28.453
We certainly didn't agree
to any kind of exclusivity.

16:28.554 --> 16:30.818
No hickeys or pins...

16:30.923 --> 16:33.619
- or letterman jackets.
- You and I are in a relationship, Alan.

16:33.726 --> 16:37.025
The fact that you don't realize it
doesn't give you license to be unfaithful.

16:37.129 --> 16:38.858
You're mad as a hatter.

16:38.964 --> 16:40.898
When two people sleep together-

16:41.000 --> 16:43.867
- That was a night terror thing.
- I'm talking about the sex.

16:43.969 --> 16:47.370
- What sex?
- The sex you and I both know is coming.

16:48.540 --> 16:50.269
Don't fall for her, Alan.

16:51.110 --> 16:53.374
She's just a guest star.

16:57.049 --> 17:01.008
He seemed to bejust staring at
one of the houses. It seemed very odd.

17:01.120 --> 17:04.351
We, uh, asked him for identification,
and he refused to provide it.

17:04.455 --> 17:06.446
- And then what happened?
- We asked him again.

17:06.558 --> 17:10.050
He continued to refuse.
So we attempted to take him into custody.

17:10.162 --> 17:16.067
That's when he became violent. We eventually
overcame him and placed him under arrest.

17:16.167 --> 17:19.035
When you arrived at the scene,
did you ask him what he was doing?

17:19.137 --> 17:23.233
He said he found the houses on this street
quite beautiful, and he enjoyed looking at them.

17:23.342 --> 17:27.368
And is that lawful in this neighborhood,
to look at houses that you find beautiful?

17:27.479 --> 17:29.879
- Of course.
- Is it your pattern...

17:29.982 --> 17:33.440
to ask people for identification
when they're engaging in lawful behavior?

17:33.552 --> 17:36.043
- He didn't live there. So I thought-
- How did you know that?

17:36.155 --> 17:40.285
I patrol that neighborhood. I pretty much
know who lives there and who doesn't.

17:40.392 --> 17:42.792
You know everybody in this neighborhood?
Every person?

17:42.895 --> 17:46.922
- Not every person, but-
- How did you know my client didn't live there?

17:49.601 --> 17:52.331
We have the right
to ask citizens for identification.

17:52.438 --> 17:54.736
That's all I did.

17:54.840 --> 17:57.308
You know what?

17:57.409 --> 18:00.310
I checked you out.
You're an exemplary officer.

18:00.412 --> 18:03.108
You also have
a reputation for honesty.

18:03.215 --> 18:06.343
Honestly, Officer...

18:06.452 --> 18:08.920
your decision to ask my client
for identification-

18:09.021 --> 18:10.921
Was his race a factor?

18:14.560 --> 18:18.963
