if he gets any kind of conviction.

18:59.872 --> 19:03.137
Shirley, surely-
Shirley, he'll be convicted of something.

19:03.242 --> 19:06.439
Well, it can't be a felony.
There's a clause in the partnership agreement.

19:06.545 --> 19:09.378
It's serious, Alan.
The partners seem inclined to expunge him.

19:09.481 --> 19:12.575
- Well, his name is on the wall.
- They'll keep the name and broom him.

19:12.684 --> 19:16.245
I see no way of dodging this
short of you having sex with the judge.

19:16.355 --> 19:20.382
I'm sorry. I now feel queasy
having even thought of that.

19:20.492 --> 19:22.858
What about the victim?
Can he be influenced?

19:22.961 --> 19:26.192
I doubt it. Even if he consented to being shot...

19:26.298 --> 19:29.392
which he seemingly did,
that still doesn't absolve Denny.

19:29.501 --> 19:32.595
- Do you have a plan?
- At the moment, no.

19:34.606 --> 19:37.234
- So stupid.
- Then why are you being so-

19:37.342 --> 19:40.834
Because I'm being stupid.
It's like frickin' high school, for God sakes.

19:40.946 --> 19:43.039
Okay. Tell me exactly what happened.

19:43.148 --> 19:46.208
I told you. I was on a date.
It was a terrific date.

19:46.318 --> 19:50.118
With another woman?
Where do you find all these women anyway?

19:50.222 --> 19:53.521
I'm a lawyer. I was a marine. Just do the math.
I'm the complete package.

19:53.625 --> 19:57.061
- Right. So-
- So I get to her front step.

19:57.162 --> 19:59.858
Clearly she would have
received my kissing her.

19:59.965 --> 20:02.433
I wanted to kiss her.
I was going to kiss her.

20:02.534 --> 20:04.593
But I didn't, because
I have this new phobia.

20:04.703 --> 20:07.866
I mean-
Right? That's what the stupid song says.

20:07.973 --> 20:12.933
What, um, exactly
are you doing when you kiss?

20:13.045 --> 20:16.947
- I do what everybody else does.
- Yeah. E-Exactly what?

20:18.417 --> 20:20.908
Lips meet. At some point,
I put my tongue in.

20:21.019 --> 20:22.953
Swish it around a little.

20:24.690 --> 20:27.420
Ah. Well, maybe you could use
some pointers or something.

20:27.526 --> 20:30.051
I happen to be
a very advanced kisser.

20:30.162 --> 20:32.824
- Maybe I can walk you through this a little.
- Don't be ridiculous.

20:32.931 --> 20:35.559
- Beats having a phobia.
- No, it doesn't.

20:35.667 --> 20:37.464
Fine.

20:43.275 --> 20:45.106
Don't even ask.

20:50.082 --> 20:52.846
Mr. Pryor, why were you
in that neighborhood?

20:52.951 --> 20:56.751
I like to dream.
One dream- I guess my American dream-

20:56.855 --> 20:59.585
is someday I would like to
live in a home like those.

20:59.691 --> 21:02.683
I enjoy the architecture,
the landscaping.

21:02.794 --> 21:06.525
You realize a police officer
has the right to ask for identification?

21:06.632 --> 21:09.829
And if I would've been doing anything suspect,
I would've given it to him.

21:09.935 --> 21:12.335
If it would've been a random thing,
I would've complied.

21:12.437 --> 21:15.463
But it wasn't. I was targeted
because I was the wrong color.

21:15.574 --> 21:19.101
But, Mr. Pryor, come on.
You physically resisted the police officers.

21:19.211 --> 21:22.180
I never assaulted them.
I just-

21:24.783 --> 21:27.843
When they pushed me to the ground
and tried to handcuff me...

21:27.953 --> 21:29.887
I simply fought back.

21:29.988 --> 21:33.947
If a police officer sees a man he believes
to be a stranger in the neighborhood...

21:34.059 --> 21:37.961
and that man is strangely staring
at houses for no apparent reason...

21:38.063 --> 21:41.123
is it your testimony that it's unreasonable
to ask that man his name?

21:41.233 --> 21:43.701
It's not reasonable to ask him
simply because he's black.

21:43.802 --> 21:46.828
If the man had been white,
staring at the houses...

21:46.938 --> 21:48.838
it would be okay to ask his name?

21:48.940 --> 21:52.501
If he would've been white,
he wouldn't have been asked. That's my point.

21:56.014 --> 21:58.574
- Plead guilty?
- They've offered probation.

21:58.684 --> 22:01.016
- You're asking me to plead guilty?
- Mr. Pryor...

22:01.119 --> 22:03.644
your testimony went well,
but let's not kid ourselves.

22:03.755 --> 22:07.247
Under the law, police can
constitutionally require identification...

22:07.359 --> 22:10.692
without probable cause,
without reasonable suspicion.

22:10.796 --> 22:13.731
- How can that be?
- Because the public wants to feel safe.

22:13.832 --> 22:17.598
And people, especially the white ones,
don't want the black ones staring at their homes.

22:17.703 --> 22:21.537
Now, we can keep fighting here,
but you must know the law does not support us.

22:21.640 --> 22:24.370
I want to fight.

22:38.490 --> 22:41.050
- How's it looking?
- Not good, Denny.

22:41.159 --> 22:44.458
- Oh.
- Aside from the case at hand...

22:44.563 --> 22:47.862
we've got your rather colorful history
of shooting people.

22:47.966 --> 22:49.433
Hmm.

22:49.534 --> 22:53.402
- There was the man in the office last year.
- He took you hostage.

22:53.505 --> 22:55.405
- Paintball incident.
- He threw a rock at me.

22:55.507 --> 22:59.204
- Your own client.
- In the knee.

22:59.311 --> 23:03.407
It simply won't be a big leap for a jury
to think you'd happily plug your therapist.

23:03.515 --> 23:05.483
I know. I know.

23:05.584 --> 23:08.314
It's, uh- It's different
this time. I...

23:08.420 --> 23:11.821
shot a human being-
a real human being.

23:11.923 --> 23:16.724
- The others weren't?
