27:05.423 --> 27:06.583
- Ooh.
- What?

27:06.691 --> 27:09.626
Well, um, this part here-
That is the most sensitive.

27:09.728 --> 27:11.889
You don't taste food with the tip.

27:11.997 --> 27:15.296
And this part is the most sensual.

27:15.400 --> 27:18.369
Well, how do people connect with
that part without slobbering?

27:18.470 --> 27:22.668
They just- Okay, could I please
show you clinically?

27:22.774 --> 27:26.107
- What do you mean?
- I mean, Brad, that I am a double black diamond kisser.

27:26.211 --> 27:29.203
And I'm also incredibly busy.
So could I please just quickly show you?

27:29.314 --> 27:31.145
- I guess. If-
- Okay.

27:35.020 --> 27:37.580
Okay. Okay, relax.

27:37.689 --> 27:40.886
The tongue isn't supposed to get hard.
I think that could be your problem.

27:42.694 --> 27:44.252
Okay.

27:49.300 --> 27:51.268
Okay. Better.

27:51.369 --> 27:54.497
Um, definitely better.
But tone down the swishing.

27:54.606 --> 27:58.736
And, um, I feel like you're blocking
my tongue from going into your mouth.

27:58.843 --> 28:00.902
- Yeah, I don't like that.
- What?

28:01.012 --> 28:05.813
- I don't like it when a woman's tongue goes in my mouth.
- Um, Brad, that's the whole idea.

28:05.917 --> 28:09.944
- Yours and hers, and hers- - I just prefer
that everything takes place in her mouth.

28:10.055 --> 28:11.955
- Why?
- Because I do.

28:12.057 --> 28:16.517
Brad, this is why you are the worst kisser
in the history of the planet.

28:16.628 --> 28:20.029
- So drop the Homeland Security, and let the girl's tongue in.
- All right.

28:20.131 --> 28:22.725
Relax. Code yellow.

28:31.910 --> 28:37.075
- Wow.
- Wow, definitely. No questions asked. Wow.

28:37.182 --> 28:38.911
Let's try it again.

28:39.017 --> 28:41.042
Mmm.

28:43.655 --> 28:45.885
Mmm. Mmm.

28:45.990 --> 28:48.185
Um-

28:48.293 --> 28:51.319
You're a-
You're a really quick study.

28:51.429 --> 28:53.294
Wow.

28:54.899 --> 28:57.959
- Uh, let's put it together. You and me. Me and you.
- I, um-

28:58.069 --> 28:59.730
I don't think that-

29:01.239 --> 29:03.207
Mmm!

29:03.308 --> 29:06.300
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
This lesson does not include hands.

29:23.595 --> 29:25.995
Do you swear to tell
the truth, the whole truth...

29:26.097 --> 29:28.588
- and nothing but the truth, so help you God?
- Yes, I do.

29:30.368 --> 29:33.303
Good afternoon, Dr. Fields.
Thank you forjoining us.

29:33.404 --> 29:35.668
I realize you've been
through quite an ordeal.

29:35.774 --> 29:38.834
Yes. And now you seek
to put me through another.

29:38.943 --> 29:40.604
Your Honor, Dr. Fields is hostile.

29:40.712 --> 29:42.475
Why wouldn't he be?
He was shot.

29:42.580 --> 29:46.311
No. I mean as in hostile witness.
Uh, permit me to lead.

29:46.417 --> 29:50.148
- Oh, go on then.
- Dr. Fields, at the time of the incident...

29:50.255 --> 29:54.021
Mr. Crane was in the middle
of a therapy session with you.

29:54.125 --> 29:56.491
- Am I correct?
- Denny Crane doesn't even believe in therapy.

29:56.594 --> 29:59.620
He comes out of boredom.
He likes to hear himself talk.

29:59.731 --> 30:02.529
- Which is the cause of great frustration for you.
- Yes.

30:02.634 --> 30:04.625
'Cause when he's not
endlessly repeating his name...

30:04.736 --> 30:06.897
he's full of this
self-serving blather.

30:07.005 --> 30:11.669
If I have to hear him go on
one more time about mad cow-

30:11.776 --> 30:13.801
This time he was less boring.
He pulled a gun.

30:13.912 --> 30:18.076
Yes. Well, the gun. The gun. If I had a nickel
for every time he did that-

30:18.183 --> 30:22.347
- Wait. He's drawn a gun on you before?
- Oh. Oh! Hell, yes.

30:22.453 --> 30:25.980
Any time he doesn't like what he hears, yes,
it's Dirty Harry time.

30:26.090 --> 30:29.890
So you really didn't feel threatened
when he produced a firearm this time then?

30:29.994 --> 30:32.224
I felt threatened to the extent...

30:32.330 --> 30:35.265
that this time it might just go off,
the way he waves it around.

30:35.366 --> 30:38.733
Okay. But, Doctor, you produced a gun
of your own, didn't you?

30:38.837 --> 30:40.930
- Absolutely I did, yes.
- Why?

30:41.039 --> 30:42.700
Because I just did.
That's why.

30:42.807 --> 30:46.208
Okay? I was sick ofhis antics,
and I told him so.

30:46.311 --> 30:48.871
You called him an empty sack,
told him he led a meaningless life.

30:48.980 --> 30:51.676
You provoked him
to pull his gun, didn't you?

30:51.783 --> 30:53.546
Maybe so. I don't know.
Who cares?

30:53.651 --> 30:57.052
What is this poopycock?
What kind of doctor are you?

30:57.155 --> 30:58.884
Your Honor, if I may proceed?

30:58.990 --> 31:01.254
Oh, go on then.

31:01.359 --> 31:06.422
Dr. Fields, once Mr. Crane
produced his weapon, you drew yours.

31:06.531 --> 31:09.466
And you told him if he didn't shoot you,
you'd shoot him.

31:09.567 --> 31:13.731
- Did you not say that, sir?
- Obviously. You know that I did.

31:13.838 --> 31:16.568
You wanted him to shoot you
so you wouldn't have to shoot yourself...

31:16.674 --> 31:20.872
and your family could collect the life insurance
to pay for your son's Ivy League education.

31:20.979 --> 31:22.913
Well, it certainly
sounds like you were there.

31:23.014 --> 31:24.777
You gave him to the count of three.

31:24.883 --> 31:27.078
Shoot you by the count of three
or you'd kill him.

31:27.185 --> 31:29.312
- That's right. Mm-hmm.
- And you counted it off.

31:29.420 --> 31:31.718
- One, two-
- And three.

31:31.823 --> 31:34.291
- Don't anybody leave this room.
- What is this jibber-jabber?

31:34.392 --> 31:36.952
- Shut up! - That wouldn't be
jibber-jabber, Your Honor. That's a gun.

31:37.061 --> 31:39.996
Anybody leaves this room,
and I will shoot Mr. Shore.

31:40.098 --> 31:43.295
- If I might object to that.
- How did you get in with that?

31:43.401 --> 31:46.996
My brother is a lawyer, and I came in
the back door with his bar card.

31:47.105 --> 31:49.972
- I guess the question, Dr. Fields, is why?
- Why?

31:50.074 --> 31:54.272
Because all my life
I sat in that chair.

31:54.379 --> 31:56.176
That's why.

31:56.281 --> 31:59.512
Listening to other people who had lives
far more grander than mine...

31:59.617 --> 32:03.917
while I just sat tucked away
in my office leading no life at all.

32:04.022 --> 32:07.685
Vicariously coaching other people,
watching them get rich like this-

32:07.792 --> 32:09.623
this nutcase here!

32:09.727 --> 32:12.491
And I couldn't stand it anymore!

32:12.597 --> 32:14.861
I did crack!
I wasn't gonna just stand around...

32:14.966 --> 32:20.097
being some- some sort of impotent
little spectator to my own life!

32:20.204 --> 32:23.264
And I'm sick of any society
that- that...

32:23.374 --> 32:27.037
glamorizes the eccentrics
and the psychopaths...

32:27.145 --> 32:30.672
and the belligerents when there's
the meek and the wise-

32:30.782 --> 32:34.684
- If I could get you to point that in any other dir-
- Shut up!

32:34.786 --> 32:38.779
You think you're the only one who likes to
live big, Denny? You think that?

32:38.890 --> 32:42.451
You think that by paying me $600 an hour
that that entitles you to belittle me?

32:42.560 --> 32:45.051
- 600?
- Shut up!

32:45.163 --> 32:47.324
You stand belittled now, Denny.

32:47.432 --> 32:50.731
Why don't I shoot your best friend here?
Why not? I mean, he's your real therapist.

32:50.835 --> 32:53.895
He's the one you tell your secrets to!
Why don't I just shoot him?

32:54.005 --> 32:58.669
- Please put the gun down.
- I didn't shoot before, Denny, but I will this time.

32:58.776 --> 33:01.074
- I really will.
- Sydney.

33:01.179 --> 33:03.841
- I took you out once. Don't make me do it again.
- With what?

33:03.948 --> 33:05.848
This!

33:13.291 --> 33:16.351
You said you'd never so much
as look at a gun again.

33:16.461 --> 33:18.429
I never said I wouldn't shoot one.

33:32.143 --> 33:36.409
I feel I should go with him.
I'm as close as he actually has to family.

33:36.514 --> 33:40.177
- Denny, you shot him twice.
- Even so. Should we ask for a continuance?

33:40.284 --> 33:42.684
No. I want to make my argument
to dismiss to the judge...

33:42.787 --> 33:44.721
while he's still
in the throes of fear.

33:44.822 --> 33:47.518
I'm due in Division Three
for closing arguments in the Pryor case.

33:47.625 --> 33:50.526
