34:30.101 --> 34:33.264
Company inkwell, Brad.
We work together. That's it.

34:33.371 --> 34:35.737
- We had sex.
- Yes.

34:35.840 --> 34:37.933
- Incredible sex.
- Yes.

34:38.042 --> 34:40.476
And that's it?

34:40.578 --> 34:43.274
Yes.

34:54.958 --> 34:58.793
Mr. Pryor refused to identification
in defiance of the law.

34:58.896 --> 35:02.696
He then physically resisted arrest,
which is a second crime.

35:02.800 --> 35:07.066
And he wasn't targeted simply because
he was black, by the way.

35:07.171 --> 35:10.937
He was questioned because he was
a stranger to a particular neighborhood.

35:11.042 --> 35:15.274
Now, did Officer Ralston come to that conclusion
in part because he was African-American?

35:15.379 --> 35:18.007
Yes. He admitted that.

35:18.116 --> 35:21.108
But where's the line between
racial profiling and common sense?

35:21.219 --> 35:23.244
